A RESOLUTION
1 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the State of Georgia so as to extend regular
2 legislative sessions to a maximum of 90 legislative days; to provide for related matters; to
3 provide for submission of this amendment for ratification or rejection; and for other
4 purposes.
5 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article III, Section IV of the Constitution is amended by revising subparagraph (a) of
8 Paragraph I as follows:
9 "(a) The Senate and House of Representatives shall organize each odd-numbered year and
10 shall be a different General Assembly for each two-year period. The General Assembly
11 shall meet in regular session on the second Monday in January of each year, or otherwise
12 as provided by law, and may continue in session for a period of no longer than 40 90 days
13 in the aggregate each year. By concurrent resolution, the General Assembly may adjourn
14 any regular session to such later date as it may fix for reconvening. Separate periods of
15 adjournment may be fixed by one or more such concurrent resolutions."
